en_2288049_0	Tuesday, July 4 – President Maithripala Sirisena has handed over appointment letters to three top-positions in the state.
en_2288049_1	The appointment letters were given for the positions of Secretary to the President, Defence Secretary and Army Commander.
en_2288049_2	Those appointed to the above positions are as follows; Austin Fernando is a former Governor to the Eastern Province and a Senior Administrative Officer.
en_2288049_3	Kapila Waidyarathne served as a Senior Additional Solicitor General prior to his appointment as the Defence Secretary.
en_2288049_4	Also, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake, the new Army Commander served as the Military Chief of Staff.
